OL,3,CGrant Shapps urges Chancellor to raise
OL,4,Cdefence spending to 2.5% of GDP
OL,6,FAs well as being lobbied by his
OL,7,Fcolleagues for extra departmental
OL,8,Fspending, Mr Hunt is under pressure to
OL,9,Fdeliver tax cuts in what could be the
OL,10,Flast fiscal statement from the
OL,11,FConservative Government before the
OL,12,Fnext general election, which is widely
OL,13,Fexpected in the autumn.
OL,15,FWith the Chancellor number-crunching
OL,16,Fover the coming days before finalising
OL,17,Fhis Budget, official forecasts of the
OL,18,FChancellor's "head room" against his
OL,19,Fplans to get borrowing to fall in five
OL,20,Fyears' time are understood to have
OL,21,Fmoved against the Government.
