OL,3,CGrant Shapps urges Chancellor to raise
OL,4,Cdefence spending to 2.5% of GDP
OL,6,FThe Cabinet minister said he could not
OL,7,Fcomment on the likely outcome for
OL,8,Fdefence when the Chancellor delivers
OL,9,Fhis Budget.
OL,11,FBut he stressed the UK is committed to
OL,12,Fmoving defence spending to 2.5% of GDP
OL,13,Fwhen the economy allows.
OL,15,FHe added: "I have personally talked
OL,16,Fabout 3% before I was defence
OL,17,Fsecretary and I think, ultimately,
OL,18,Fcountries will need to spend more.
