OL,3,CGrant Shapps urges Chancellor to raise
OL,4,Cdefence spending to 2.5% of GDP
OL,6,FA Treasury spokesman said: "We have
OL,7,Fprovided the Ministry of Defence the
OL,8,Flargest sustained spending increase
OL,9,Fsince the end of the Cold War, with a
OL,10,F#24 billion uplift in cash terms over
OL,11,Fthe spending review 2020 period.
OL,13,F"At the spring Budget last year we
OL,14,Falso provided an extra #11 billion
OL,15,Fover the next five years.
OL,17,F"Our aspiration over the longer term
OL,18,Fis to invest 2.5% of GDP on defence as
OL,19,Fsoon as the fiscal and economic
OL,20,Fcircumstances allow."
